node.text:
In order to stretch our capacities and grow as humans, we are required to do things we haven’t yet done.

Imposter syndrome is something we all feel when we’re pushing these boundaries and treading into not-yet-known territory. Everyone feels this same thing. When you realize this, you won’t have any reason left to stop yourself. 

#impostersyndrome #personalgrowth #trusttheprocess

🎥 by @maxwmccoy
🎶 "Remember Jah" by the incredible @satsang

node.title: How To Push Past Self-Imposed Boundaries

node.text:
This past trimester in @fit.for.service we have been training to cultivate the full expression of the sacred masculine. Our journey through the Austin summit started with a poetry workshop by the great @inqlife where we learned to alchemize our grievances into gratitude through the medium of spoken word. We entered workshops where we explored the complicated nuances of the psyche, and prepared ourselves to retrain the harsh inner critic into a loving and supportive inner coach. 

To test what we had been learning, we created the Elemental Games. Five teams were charged with representing the five Earth elements with costume and dance, and then offered the opportunity to represent their team in competition. It was one of the most powerful ceremonies any of us have ever been a part of. Before the paint washed off, we came together with a deeper appreciation for every single person who entered the arena. 

We enjoyed a stunning private concert with @satsang, a night of sober celebration, and one of the most potent speeches I have ever heard by the philosopher king Charles Eisenstein. 

I’m so grateful to everyone who participated in Trimester 2. And as my teacher Don Howard always said, there is always another layer. We’ll go together to find that layer this October in Sedona for Trimester 3. If you are interested in applying, click the link in bio or head to aubreymarcus.com/fitforservice

🎥 by @maxwmccoy

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Aubrey Marcus in Austin, Texas. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'Aubrey Marcus @AubreyMarcus The boy thinks, the man knows. The boy is friendly, the man is a friend. The boy answers, the man questions. The boy likes, the man loves. The boy hopes, the man trusts. The boy is theatrical, the man is magical. The boy tries the man does. 9:53 PM 8/13/21 Twitter Web App'.

node.text:
I may have some gray hairs in my beard, but I still got a lot of boy in me. 🤷

And that’s all good, because above all the man accepts himself. 

Also “boy” and “man” are just ways to express the idea of maturity. Don’t be distracted by the gender or associations with the words🤎

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Aubrey Marcus in Austin, Texas. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'Aubrey Marcus @AubreyMarcus Commitment is the end of questioning. It is go until you fail, fix it until it is unfixable, with your shield or on it. Commitment is scary. But the gift of commitment is that when you are committed, there is no torturous anxiety about what you should do.'.

node.text:
It's not always easy for me to commit. 

If I give myself an out, often times I will take it. But the best things in my life have come from my deepest commitments.

So what would you like to commit to?

#committed #stayfocused #commitment

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Aubrey Marcus in Austin, Texas. May be an image of text that says 'Shame Can Only Survive In The Shadow of Silence What are you ashamed of? What do you judge yourself for? Find someone you can share your truth with, and liberate yourself. You don't need to carry the burden of your secrets. Are you ready to be be free?'.

node.text:
During a guided meditation with a powerful healer, my mind conjured up the image of Jesus. He asked me why I was sad. I explained to him all of my fears, my feelings of not doing enough, all of the ways in which I could be better. He put his hand lovingly on my head, and said the most powerful words he could say. "Me too."

Everything you are experiencing, we are all experiencing. Maybe you have it a little more or less than I do, but I promise when I look inside myself I can find the same thing as you. When you realize this, no matter what someone tells you, you won't flinch. Give yourself this gift of freedom. And be the sanctuary for all of your friends and family to liberate themselves as well. 

#shame #judgement #forgiveness

node.text:
In order to stretch our capacities and grow as humans, we are required to do things we haven’t yet done.

Imposter syndrome is something we all feel when we’re pushing these boundaries and treading into not-yet-known territory. Everyone feels this same thing. When you realize this, you won’t have any reason left to stop yourself. 

#impostersyndrome #personalgrowth #trusttheprocess

🎥 by @maxwmccoy
🎶 "Remember Jah" by the incredible @satsang

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Aubrey Marcus in Austin, Texas. May be an image of text that says 'Truth Is A Frequency The body is the perfect instrument to detect that frequency. When you encounter truth, it will be music to your nervous system. But if your body is in accord with anger, distrust, or fear... Then the only thing that will FEEL true is more anger, distrust, and fear. Reset your instrument by attuning to Love.'.

node.text:
Truth and Love are synonyms, because real Love is always true. I'm not talking about the "I need you to validate me" love. Or the "I really want to have sex with you" love. I'm talking about the "I just want you to be happy no matter what" kind of Love.

This is our true state, because the truth at the bottom of everything is that we are all each other, living a different life. This is why Love is the true substrate of our existence. By tuning to Love, you are tuning to Truth.

#truth #love #resonance

node.text:
The mind is inconceivably powerful. It can work for you, or if left unchecked, it can become your worst enemy. 

Harnessing the power of the mind during difficult challenges can help you to overcome any stressor or obstacle. 

From my latest podcast with Rich Daviney.

Link In Bio. 

#challenge #thepowerofthemind #overcomeobstacles

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Aubrey Marcus in Austin, Texas. May be an image of text that says 'We create an internal judge, harsher than the one who has judged us the most in our life... In order to protect ourselves from their punishment. But the problem with this strategy is that we end up punishing ourselves far more than anyone could ever punish us. And for most of us, that punishing external judge is no longer a part of our lives anymore.'.

node.text:
Our mind is not random. Our behavior has a reason. Try to identify the harshest judge in your life. The one who punished you the most to try to get you to be how they wanted you to be.

Most of the time this punishment administered was the removal of love. It was so painful, we created a mechanism that removes love from ourself, to teach us not to do the thing that would cause us to be punished.

It makes sense, but it’s a shit strategy. The good news is that with awareness we can change the mechanism. We can start to be the loving coach, rather than the maniacal judge. It just takes patience to rewire what has been built over years.

#selflove #healing #mindfulness

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Aubrey Marcus in Austin, Texas. May be an image of text that says 'August 23, 2021 at 9:04 AM Trying to be popular is like trying to sit on a bicycle without peddling. It takes constant adjustments to keep from falling. But if you just start going, headed in a direction that is medningful to you, one day you'll look up and see that other people are watching. Some of them will be inspired by you to chart their own course. Some, too afraid to make the journey, will throw rocks at you as you pass by.'.

node.text:
The freedom is in surrendering to the ride. Knowing where you are going, and just going there. You can take pictures of what you are doing, or write essays or books about it, but that’s not why you are riding.

You are riding because peddling toward that thing IS your destination. It isn’t about arriving somewhere, it’s about being on the road.

Those with rusted bicycles, too scared of the journey they are called to, will try to knock you down with their hate. But they have no power you do not give them.

You will never receive hate from another rider. Just a nod of appreciation, from a fellow traveler of the way.
